hopobject.body: We'd like to offer you the job order growth factor plus Organizers have suggested the show could surpass the all-time pay-per-view record of 2.44 million buys and spawn greater profits than the previous high of $130 million both achieved when Mayweather beat Oscar De La Hoya in 2007. The event has already been sold out for months, producing the greatest live gate total in boxing history with $19.1 million, besting the previous record of $18,419,200.
